Subject:Re: [Antenna-discussion] 1/2-wave vertical really needsagroundplane?
Richard

You ought to know that capacitors can be explained perfectly without
the use of a notional current flowing between the plates.  Capacitors
have been used to illustrate the idea of displacement currents but I
believe it has not helped anyone's understanding of displacement
currents, indeed it has caused a lot of confusion.

The concept is necessary in explaining radio waves, but not capacitors.

Alan G3NOQ




On 9 November 2012 00:03, Richard Fry <rfry@adams.net> wrote:
