>
> Then shouldn't your declaration above preclude the existence/usefulness of
> a-c currents conveyed between the terminals of all air-insulated capacitors?
>
> And if such was true, how then would you explain the known performance of
> such circuital elements based on their passage of a-c current from one its
> terminals to the other?
>
